items.title: Mercury's poles may be icier than scientists thought
items.summary: A new study identifies three large surface ice deposits near Mercury's north pole, and suggests there could be many additional small-scale deposits that would dramatically increase the planet's surface ice inventory.

items.title: Winner takes all: Success enhances taste for luxury goods, study suggests
items.summary: Footballers in flashy cars, City workers in Armani suits, reality TV celebrities sipping expensive champagne while sitting in hot tubs: what drives people to purchase luxury goods? New research suggests that it may be a sense of being a 'winner' -- but that contrary to expectations, it is not driven by testosterone.

alternate.title: Winner takes all: Success enhances taste for luxury goods, study suggests
